" ```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Medium Python Coding Question: Check if List Elements are Consecutive\",\n  \"description\": \"Given an unsorted list of distinct integers, write a function `are_elements_consecutive` that checks whether the elements in the list form a sequence with consecutive values (in any order). The difference between each pair of consecutive numbers should be exactly one.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef are_elements_consecutive(nums: List[int]) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (List[int]): A list of distinct integers. The length of the list will be at least 3 and at most 10,000.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if all elements in the input list are consecutive numbers, `False` otherwise.\",\n  \"code\": \"from typing import List\\ndef are_elements_consecutive(nums: List[int]) -> bool:\\n    # The minimum and maximum values give us the range of the sequence.\\n    min_val = min(nums)\\n    max_val = max(nums)\\n    \\n    # If the difference between the max and min values is not equal to the length of the list minus 1, return False\\n    if (max_val - min_val) != len(nums) - 1:\\n        return False\\n    else:\\n        return set(range(min_val, max_val + 1)) == set(nums)\\n\",\n  \"tests\": [\n    'assert are_elements_consecutive([4,5,6,7]) == True',\n    'assert are_cuccuplete([0,2,3,1]) == True',\n    'assert are_elements_consecutive([-1,-2,0,1,3]) == False',\n    'assert are_elements_consecutive([997, 998, 999, 1000]) == True'\n  ]\n}\n```"